    "details": {
      "isComplex": false,
      "level": {
        "value": 9
      },
      "disable": "<p>@Check[type:thievery|dc:30] (master) to destroy the correct carvings or a successful dispel magic (5th level; counteract DC 25) to deactivate the script's magic.</p>",
      "description": "<p>An intricate scripture winds around the carvings, coiling across them and along the walls like an immensely long tangle of ribbons.</p><hr /><h3>Conversion notes (this module)</h3><p>Coded Thassilonian wall-text (@Check[type:religion|dc:31] + the language and 10 minutes to decipher) that claims to warn of perils — and self-alters so it can never be finished. Ancient Shoanti skeletons (their gear: <strong>+1 hide armor, a +1 striking frost earth breaker, a +1 striking returning totem spear</strong>) died of thirst mid-sentence here.</p>",
